# Settlement Summary

Produce a standalone summary of settlement history and material terms with clear implementation steps.

## Prerequisites

1. Final settlement agreement or executed term sheet
2. Negotiation record: emails, draft redlines, mediation notes
3. Case caption, parties, counsel, and matter identifiers
4. Settlement consideration details and payment timelines
5. Any court-approval requirements or dismissal procedures

## Output Structure / Process

Use the following structure and tables.

## Executive Summary

Include in 2-3 short paragraphs:
- Parties and matter
- Nature of dispute and resolution date
- Consideration (monetary and non-monetary)
- Status of execution and effectiveness

## Negotiation Chronology

| Date | Event | Offer/Counter | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| YYYY-MM-DD | Initial demand | $ | Key terms |
| YYYY-MM-DD | Mediation | $ | Breakthroughs |
| YYYY-MM-DD | Agreement in principle | $ | Open issues |

## Material Terms

| Term | Details |
|---|---|
| Consideration | Amount, form, and allocation |
| Payment schedule | Dates, method, contingencies |
| Releases | Releasing parties, released parties |
| Claims released | Enumerated claims or categories |
| Carve-outs | Claims preserved or excluded |
| Dismissal | With/without prejudice; filings required |
| Confidentiality | Scope, exceptions, permitted disclosures |
| Non-disparagement | Scope, duration, remedies |
| No admission | Clause summary |
| Tax treatment | Allocation language or 1099 terms |
| Attorneys’ fees | Who pays; caps or waivers |
| Indemnity | Scope, duration, triggers |
| Future conduct | Business terms or restrictive covenants |
| Dispute resolution | Forum, venue, governing law |

## Releases and Preservation

| Item | Scope | Exceptions |
|---|---|---|
| Parties released | List all releasing/released entities | |
| Claims released | Known/unknown; statutory/common law | |
| Claims preserved | Explicit exclusions | |

## Conditions Precedent / Approvals

Checklist:
- Court approval required (class action, minors, derivatives)
- Lien resolution or insurer consent
- Confidentiality acknowledgments executed
- Dismissal papers drafted and approved

## Implementation Plan

| Task | Owner | Deadline | Dependency |
|---|---|---|---|
| Execute agreement | | | |
| First payment | | | |
| File dismissal | | | |
| Tax docs issued | | | |
| Close file / archive | | | |

## Open Items / Risks

List unresolved issues, contingencies, or compliance risks that could delay effectiveness.

## Guidelines

- Stay neutral; describe negotiations without advocacy.
- Use exact amounts, dates, and party names; avoid rounding.
- Flag any missing documents or ambiguous terms.
- Do not quote privileged communications verbatim.
- Identify any confidentiality constraints on distribution.
- Note when terms deviate materially from initial positions.
